{
  "texts": [
    "This comparative analysis builds upon the earlier discussion of application case studies by shifting the focus to a model-oriented perspective.",
    "It helps to clarify how different computational tools are matched to various sensory tasks and data types, and provides a foundation for selecting appropriate AI techniques in future sensory research.",
    "One of the critical similarities between olfaction and gustation in AI applications is the growing emphasis on data-driven flavor profiling (Malavolta et al. 2022).In both domains, large datasets that include sensory evaluations, chemical compositions, and consumer feedback are integrated into machine learning models.",
    "This integration helps identify complex interactions among compounds and predict sensory outcomes.",
    "For instance, AI-based regression and classification techniques are widely used to infer how molecular variations influence perceived flavor, which supports targeted formulation in food and beverage development."
  ]
}